Scorpio (♏) (Greek: Σκορπιός, "Skorpios", Latin: "Scorpio") is the eighth astrological sign in the Zodiac.
It spans the 210-240th degree of the zodiac, between 207.25 and 234.75 degree of celestial longitude, an area which the Sun transits on average between October 23 and November 22 each year.
In Sidereal astrology, the sun currently transits the constellation of Scorpio from November 16 to December 15 (approximately). Individuals born during these dates, depending on which system of astrology they subscribe to, may be called "Scorpios".
Associations.
In astrology, a planet's domicile is the zodiac sign over which it has rulership. The traditional planet said to be ruler of Scorpio, or associated with Scorpios, is Mars. but most modern astrologers use Pluto as ruler.
